Exxon Offers 50 Percent Stake in Indonesian Coalbed Gas Project

-- B y   J o e   C a r r o l l
-- 
2011-07-19T15:47:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-19/exxon-offers-50-percent-stake-in-indonesian-coalbed-gas-project.html
Exxon Mobil Corp. (XOM) , the world’s
largest company, is seeking partners to help develop a natural-
gas project in  Indonesia .  Exxon is offering a 50 percent stake in its Kalimantan
coalbed-methane project, located in three exploration blocks,
the Irving, Texas-based company said in an  announcement  posted
today on Schlumberger Ltd.’s IndigoPool website.  Exxon said initial drilling on the blocks showed
“encouraging” results.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Joe Carroll in  Chicago  at 
 jcarroll8@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Susan Warren at   susanwarren@bloomberg.net . 